  "title": "Event: Annual Conference 2025",
  "subject": "SAGP | Annual Conference 2025",
  "rich_html": "<!doctype html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>SAGP | Annual Conference 2025</title>\n</head>\n<body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#f6f1e8;font-family:Georgia,'Times New Roman',serif;color:#2d251b;\">\n  <div style=\"max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:42px 24px;\">\n    <div style=\"display:none;max-height:0;overflow:hidden;opacity:0;color:transparent;\">\n      The 2025 SAGP Annual Conference brings scholars together for four thematic sessions over two days, each moderated by a senior scholar and centered on original research in Ancient Greek philosophy.\n\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"background:#fffaf0;border:1px solid #d8c6a3;border-radius:20px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 14px 40px rgba(45,37,27,.10);\">\n\n      <div style=\"text-align:center;padding:34px 42px 28px;border-bottom:1px solid #e4d4b8;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:34px;line-height:1;margin-bottom:10px;\">🏛️</div>\n\n        <div style=\"font-size:30px;letter-spacing:.08em;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px;\">\n          SAGP\n        </div>\n\n        <div style=\"font-size:16px;color:#6b5a45;\">\n          Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      \n      <div style=\"padding:40px 42px 30px;border-bottom:1px solid #e4d4b8;\">\n        <p style=\"text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.16em;color:#9a6a1f;font-size:13px;margin:0 0 14px;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\">\n          SAGP Event\n        </p>\n\n        <h1 style=\"font-size:38px;line-height:1.12;margin:0 0 18px;font-weight:500;\">\n          Annual Conference 2025\n        </h1>\n\n        <p style=\"font-size:20px;line-height:1.5;margin:0;color:#5d5144;\">\n          The 2025 SAGP Annual Conference brings scholars together for four thematic sessions over two days, each moderated by a senior scholar and centered on original research in Ancient Greek philosophy.\n\n        </p>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"padding:36px 42px;\">\n        \n\n        <h2 style=\"font-size:23px;margin:0 0 14px;font-weight:500;\">\n          Event Details\n        </h2>\n\n        <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;margin:0 0 28px;\">\n          <tr>\n            <td style=\"padding:13px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #eadcc4;font-size:17px;\"><strong>Date</strong></td>\n            <td style=\"padding:13px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #eadcc4;text-align:right;font-size:17px;\">\n              November 15, 2025\n               - November 16, 2025\n            </td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td style=\"padding:13px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #eadcc4;font-size:17px;\"><strong>Location</strong></td>\n            <td style=\"padding:13px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #eadcc4;text-align:right;font-size:17px;\">\n              Zoom\n              <br><span style=\"font-size:14px;color:#8a6d43;\">PST</span>\n            </td>\n          </tr>\n        </table>\n\n        \n          <h2 style=\"font-size:23px;margin:34px 0 14px;font-weight:500;\">\n            Program\n          </h2>\n\n          \n            <div style=\"padding:18px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #eadcc4;\">\n              <h3 style=\"font-size:20px;margin:0 0 6px;font-weight:500;\">\n                Plato: Learning in the Dialogues\n              </h3>\n\n              <p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;color:#6b5a45;font-size:15px;\">\n                November 15, 2025\n                 · 07:00\n                 PST\n              </p>\n\n              \n                <ul style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.55;padding-left:22px;margin:0;\">\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>Protagorean vs. Aristotelian political wisdom</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Mitzi Lee</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>Nostos from the Land of Zalmoxis: Socrates, Learner and Teacher</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">David Murphy</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>War (Not) a ‘Violent Teacher’: Socrates and the (Mis)Teachings of Warfare</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Andrea Capra</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                </ul>\n              \n            </div>\n          \n            <div style=\"padding:18px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #eadcc4;\">\n              <h3 style=\"font-size:20px;margin:0 0 6px;font-weight:500;\">\n                Aristotle’s Categories\n              </h3>\n\n              <p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;color:#6b5a45;font-size:15px;\">\n                November 15, 2025\n                 · 11:00\n                 PST\n              </p>\n\n              \n                <ul style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.55;padding-left:22px;margin:0;\">\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>Individuals in Aristotle’s Categories</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Fred D. Miller, Jr.</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>Categories in H.2</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Christian Pfeiffer</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                </ul>\n              \n            </div>\n          \n            <div style=\"padding:18px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #eadcc4;\">\n              <h3 style=\"font-size:20px;margin:0 0 6px;font-weight:500;\">\n                Presocratic Ontology in and after Parmenides\n              </h3>\n\n              <p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;color:#6b5a45;font-size:15px;\">\n                November 16, 2025\n                 · 07:00\n                 PST\n              </p>\n\n              \n                <ul style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.55;padding-left:22px;margin:0;\">\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>Only now: the puzzle of Parmenides B8.5–6</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Matthew Evans</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>Being, the full and the rare: Parmenides, the post-Parmenideans and the concept of body</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Gábor Betegh</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>Ontology and epistemology of colours after Parmenides: Empedocles, Anaxagoras, Democritus</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Maria Michela Sassi</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                </ul>\n              \n            </div>\n          \n            <div style=\"padding:18px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #eadcc4;\">\n              <h3 style=\"font-size:20px;margin:0 0 6px;font-weight:500;\">\n                Epistemology and Ontology in Stoicism\n              </h3>\n\n              <p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;color:#6b5a45;font-size:15px;\">\n                November 16, 2025\n                 · 11:00\n                 PST\n              </p>\n\n              \n                <ul style=\"font-size:16px;line-height:1.55;padding-left:22px;margin:0;\">\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>Having the impression of something: the grasp of corporeal and incorporeal entities in Stoic epistemology</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Michele Alessandrelli</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>The Stoics on Perceiving What Obtains</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Christian Pineda</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                    <li>\n                      <strong>Making an Impression: Stoic incorporeals as proper objects of thought, reference, and knowledge</strong>\n                      <br><span style=\"color:#6b5a45;\">Vanessa de Harven</span>\n                    </li>\n                  \n                </ul>\n              \n            </div>\n          \n        \n\n        <p style=\"margin-top:34px;\">\n          <a href=\"https://societyforancientgreekphilosophy.org\" style=\"display:inline-block;background:#8a5a13;color:#fff;text-decoration:none;padding:13px 20px;border-radius:999px;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;\">\n            Visit the SAGP website\n          </a>\n        </p>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"padding:26px 42px;background:#2d251b;color:#f8efe0;font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;text-align:center;\">\n        <strong>Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy</strong><br>\n        <a href=\"https://societyforancientgreekphilosophy.org\" style=\"color:#f8efe0;\">\n          societyforancientgreekphilosophy.org\n        </a>\n        <br><br>\n        Visit the Society website for upcoming events, calls, membership information,\n        and Society activities.\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>",
  "plain_text": "====================================================\n\nSAGP\nSociety for Ancient Greek Philosophy\n\n====================================================\n\nAnnual Conference 2025\n\nThe 2025 SAGP Annual Conference brings scholars together for four thematic sessions over two days, each moderated by a senior scholar and centered on original research in Ancient Greek philosophy.\n\n\nDate:\nNovember 15, 2025 - November 16, 2025\n\nLocation:\nZoom (PST)\n\nSessions:\n- Plato: Learning in the Dialogues, November 15, 2025 at 07:00\n- Aristotle’s Categories, November 15, 2025 at 11:00\n- Presocratic Ontology in and after Parmenides, November 16, 2025 at 07:00\n- Epistemology and Ontology in Stoicism, November 16, 2025 at 11:00\n\nVisit the SAGP website for full details.\n\n====================================================\n\nSociety for Ancient Greek Philosophy\nhttps://societyforancientgreekphilosophy.org\n",
